The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, May 4: The government is understood to have cleared Vodafones application to acquire a majority stake in Hutch Essar. Finance minister P. Chidambaram today approved Vodafones application following the clearance by the Foreign Investment Promotion Board last week, sources said. The FIPB had cleared Vodafones deal after scrutinising the foreign shareholding in the company.

 Mumbai, May 4: Indias forex reserves increased by $254 million to $204.135 billion during the week ended April 27, against $203.881 billion in the preceding week. It had increased by $789 million during the week ended April 20.

 New Delhi, May 4 : The government has appointed Labanyendu Mansingh, former consumer affairs secretary, as the chairman of the petroleum and natural gas regulatory board to oversee the downstream oil refining and marketing sector. 

 New Delhi, May 4 : Indian Oil has signed an agreement with the Railways to allow the sale of e-tickets at 500 petrol pumps in Calcutta, Delhi, Mumbai, Chennai and Bangalore.

 Mumbai, May 4: ICICI Bank has fixed May 19 as the record date for ascertaining the eligible shareholders of Sangli Bank.




